{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"838b2de7-d1e6-4e93-9371-6f74f20ccb08","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four report the reason in test results so you can track why tests were skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"155ed943-9557-4016-816a-0fa4de68e287","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":219,"requestId":"6807:2FF63B:2B70675:2FEAEB8:69FD3A12"},"id":"05c13839-eb2e-45c1-8a1a-841145315764","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:19.782Z","parentId":"79beb8ad-a3d9-490e-bce1-7626bcd0ef5a"}
